{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"149c7e8f-421e-4668-a957-035ee77178bb","content":"No files found in the working directory, so I'll walk you through the conversion directly.\n\n## Converting to Compiled Bindings\n\nAdd `x:DataType` to your `ContentPage` root element, pointing at your ViewModel:\n\n```xml\n<ContentPage xmlns=\"http://schemas.microsoft.com/dotnet/2021/maui\"\n             xmlns:x=\"http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2009/xaml\"\n             xmlns:vm=\"clr-namespace:YourApp.ViewModels\"\n             x:Class=\"YourApp.Views.SettingsPage\"\n             x:DataType=\"vm:SettingsViewModel\">\n\n    <VerticalStackLayout Padding=\"20\" Spacing=\"15\">\n\n        <Label Text=\"{Binding Theme}\" />\n\n        <Switch IsToggled=\"{Binding NotificationsEnabled}\" />\n\n        <Label Text=\"{Binding FontSize, StringFormat='Font size: {0}'}\" />\n\n    </VerticalStackLayout>\n</ContentPage>\n```\n\nThat's it — `x:DataType` tells the XAML compiler the type of the `BindingContext`, so every `{Binding}` in scope is resolved **at compile time**. A typo like `{Binding Themee}` becomes a **build error**, not a silent runtime failure.\n\n## How to Catch Binding Errors at Build Time\n\n1. **`x:DataType` is the key.** Once declared, the compiler validates every property path under that element's scope.\n\n2. **Ensure XAML compilation is enabled** (it is by default in .NET MAUI, but verify there's no opt-out in your `.csproj`):\n   ```xml\n   <!-- This should NOT be in your csproj -->\n   <!-- <MauiXamlCInterpretation>true</MauiXamlCInterpretation> -->\n   ```\n\n3. **Nested DataTemplates** need their own `x:DataType`:\n   ```xml\n   <DataTemplate x:DataType=\"vm:ItemViewModel\">\n       <Label Text=\"{Binding Name}\" />\n   </DataTemplate>\n   ```\n\n4. **To opt out locally** (e.g., for a dynamic binding), use `x:DataType=\"x:Null\"` on that element.\n\n5. **Build the project** — any invalid property name or type mismatch will now surface as a compiler error:\n   ```\n   error XC0045: Binding: Property \"Themee\" not found on \"SettingsViewModel\"\n   ```","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"38e4a5ce-b25d-4f85-9280-1f2fbbfb4a91","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The directory is empty — there are no existing files. The user is asking me to explain how to convert a hypothetical SettingsPage.xaml to use compiled bindings. I'll provide the explanation and example code directly.","outputTokens":659,"requestId":"044C:34A53A:AD713B:C5CBE8:6A027925"},"id":"48daf18f-be86-487f-bea1-59aed3c86d1e","timestamp":"2026-05-12T00:49:54.717Z","parentId":"762d0c0d-02f9-4ac1-aa01-f85d792b3ce9"}
